articles.title: AI Construction Costs Can Be an Accounting ‘Black Box’
articles.mainIdea: AI Construction Costs Can Be an Accounting ‘Black Box’
articles.summary: The Wall Street Journal: AI Construction Costs Can Be an Accounting ‘Black Box’. Spending on chips is generally lumped together with data-center building costs on corporate balance sheets, even as the lifespan for chips can be much shorter.
